{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"7e9a024f-b7c8-4ca0-90bc-49ecda564a4d","content":"No repo-specific docs here, but this is a well-known migration. Here's what you need to do:\n\n### Remove (or set to `false`) the VSTest opt-in\n\n```xml\n<!-- Delete this line (or change to false): -->\n<UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>\n```\n\nWith **MSTest.Sdk 3.8+**, `Microsoft.Testing.Platform` is already the **default** runner, so simply removing `<UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>` activates it.\n\n### What changes at runtime\n\n| Area | VSTest | Microsoft.Testing.Platform |\n|------|--------|---------------------------|\n| Run tests | `dotnet test` | `dotnet test` (still works) |\n| Direct exe | N/A | `./YourTests.exe` works directly |\n| CLI filters | `--filter` | `--filter` (same syntax) |\n\n### Things to check\n\n1. **Remove any `<OutputType>Library</OutputType>`** — the new platform builds an executable; the SDK sets this automatically.\n2. **`.runsettings`** — still supported, but some adapter-specific nodes may need updating.\n3. **Custom test adapters / extensions** — if you reference VSTest-specific adapters (`Microsoft.VisualStudio.TestPlatform.*` packages), check for Microsoft.Testing.Platform equivalents.\n4. **CI scripts** — `dotnet test` keeps working. If you were passing `--logger trx`, switch to `--report-trx` or add the `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport` package.\n\n### TL;DR — one-line change\n\nJust **delete** `<UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>` from your `.csproj` / `Directory.Build.props`. Everything else is handled by the SDK.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"138677e8-d827-4a44-a54e-b34a2a91bfea","outputTokens":427,"requestId":"6805:B29EE:2C28778:306DF1D:69FD349E"},"id":"bbd8469a-da23-47ad-a0a3-b4d45e677ed4","timestamp":"2026-05-08T00:56:09.335Z","parentId":"d59ae3c1-a55e-4875-8efb-75dd8a97c09b"}
